sentences.english: Both made of pine; both one inch thick.
sentences.chinese: 都是由松木做成的，都是一英寸厚。

sentences.english: So they used pinewood as the foundation.
sentences.chinese: 所以建房子的人就采用松木作为地基。

sentences.english: Material: China fir or pinewood. It was sold at WalMart in America before.
sentences.chinese: 杉木，松木制作，曾在美国沃尔玛超市销售。

sentences.english: Pine lumber with many knots; used especially for paneling and furniture.
sentences.chinese: 带许多节疤的松木，尤其用作镶板和制家具。

sentences.english: The cheerful room was panelled in pine.
sentences.chinese: 这间舒适的房间镶有松木。

sentences.english: Underwater photos from some of Pinewood Studios' most famous films are to go on display for the first time.
sentences.chinese: 松木工作室最有名的水下摄影作品即将首次展出。

sentences.english: The interior walls and floors were made with pine wood finished in natural primer.
sentences.chinese: 内墙和地板为天然漆刷过的松木。

sentences.english: Then he scraped away the dirt, and exposed a pine shingle.
sentences.chinese: 5接着他刨去泥土，下面露出一块松木瓦块。

sentences.english: So Hiram gave Solomon cedar trees and fir trees according to all his desire.
sentences.chinese: 于是希兰照着所罗门所要的，给他香柏木和松木。

sentences.english: In this way Hiram kept Solomon supplied with all the cedar and pine logs he wanted
sentences.chinese: 于是希兰照着所罗门所要的，给他香柏木和松木。

sentences.english: The grey walls were divided into artificial paneling by strips of white-enameled pine.
sentences.chinese: 灰色的墙壁用漆白的松木条隔成镶板的模样。

sentences.english: One quality of pinewood is that it can be sawn easily.
sentences.chinese: 松木的一个特点是容易锯开。

sentences.english: Dye dispersant was synthesized using kraft lignin as raw material.
sentences.chinese: 以松木硫酸盐木质素为原料合成染料分散剂。

sentences.english: He rolled himself up in his blanket and wallowed in under the old pine table .
sentences.chinese: 他用毯子把自己裹起来，滚到那张老松木桌子底下去。

sentences.english: The pattern is superb displayed on a pine dresser and can be contemprised by accenting with strong, vivid colours.
sentences.chinese: 这一系列在松木碗柜上展示其效果是非凡的。
